FT  10 FEB 93 / Taiwan plans oil privatisation
Taiwan is drawing up plans to privatise its national oil company, the
government's Commission of National Corporations said yesterday, Reuter
reports from Taipei. It plans to sell a majority stake in Chinese Petroleum,
which has a monopoly on oil imports and processing, a commission spokesman
said. The government has also decided to privatise Taiwan Power, the
state-run electricity supplier, Taiwan Fertiliser and Taiwan Salt Works, he
added.
